    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 350째F (175째C).</li>
            <li>Rinse the Peking duck inside and out, and pat it dry with paper towels.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, mix hoisin sauce, soy sauce, rice vinegar, honey, sesame oil, and five-spice powder to make the glaze.</li>
            <li>Brush the duck with the glaze, ensuring an even coating.</li>
            <li>Roast the duck in the preheated oven for about 1.5 to 2 hours or until the skin is crispy and the internal temperature reaches 165째F (74째C).</li>
            <li>While the duck is roasting, warm the Mandarin pancakes according to package instructions.</li>
            <li>Once the duck is cooked, let it rest for a few minutes before carving.</li>
            <li>Serve the carved Peking duck on Mandarin pancakes, garnished with sliced green onions and cucumber strips.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Peking Duck!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

